						<!-- Continued from facing page, left margin, Ha2.179r -->
						Vnum solid&egrave; pragmaticum. In paucis libris, plurimu[m] scientia[e]: in multis,
						minimum. Quod petis, intus habes: exceptis Necessarijs;
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
				<position place="intext" book_orientation="270">
					<marginalia_text>
						paucissimis Singularibus.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>one complete pragmatic book. In a few books, there are many things of science: in many book, there is a minimum of it.
			What you strive for, you have within: with the necessary things taken out; with the fewest singular things.</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
